  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<TValue>, Collection<TValue>, List<TValue>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ArrayAsFixedSizeList

    @FullyTested
public abstract class FixedSizeForwardingList<TValue>
extends BaseFixedSizeForwardingList<TValue>
    This is a specialized form of ForwardingList that does not allow the underlying list size to change. However, elements may be modified via ForwardingList.set(int, Object).

    This class is closely related to UnmodifiableForwardingList.

    Author:
    Kevin Connor ARPE (kevinarpe@gmail.com)
    See Also:
    UnmodifiableForwardingList, BaseFixedSizeForwardingList, ForwardingList, FixedSizeListIterator
